# homelab-uptime-kuma — Environment Variables
#
# No deploy-time secrets are required for this service.
# Uptime Kuma creates its admin account on first login via the web UI.
# Credentials are stored internally by the application — not injected here.
#
# This file exists to maintain the program standard defined in STANDARDS.md
# Section 3. If environment variables are added in a future version of
# Uptime Kuma, document and add them here before committing.
